@startuml
!include ../includes/appsec-style.puml
title AppSec Process 10: COTS & SaaS Vulnerability Management (Vendor-Led Fixes)

' Purpose: Track third-party risk where you cannot directly fix code, using AppCode for accountability.

start

partition "Register" {
  :Assign/verify AppCode;
  :Record vendor + product/service;
  :Record install model + integrations;
}

partition "Monitor" {
  :Subscribe to advisories (CVE/vendor bulletins);
  :Periodic assurance review (SOC2/ISO, pen test);
  :Validate exposure (env + integration scope);
}

partition "Triage" {
  if (Vendor patch available?) then (Yes)
    :Plan upgrade window;
  else (No)
    :Request ETA + escalation;
  endif
  :Create/Update ticket (AppCode + owner);
}

partition "Mitigate" {
  :Apply config hardening;
  :Network controls / WAF;
  :Disable vulnerable features;
  :Add monitoring/detections;
}

partition "Verify & Close" {
  :Confirm patch applied or risk reduced;
  :Document evidence (AppCode);
  :Close or renew waiver with time-box;
}

note right
Key message: **You still own the risk** even when vendors own the code.
end note

stop
@enduml
